,'about',NULL,NULL,'<p>\r\n                    When people wish to experience the heavenly beauty and charm of the\r\n                    National Parks of India then they knock on the door of Jungle Safari\r\n                    India. We are one of the leading tour companies that offers various\r\n                    tour packages for different corners of India. We curate the best\r\n                    tour packages so that people can explore every corner of India\r\n                    without worrying about anything. Other than the Tour Packages we\r\n                    also provide other services including jeep safari rides, canter\r\n                    safari rides, and elephant safari rides. Furthermore, you can also\r\n                    book nice and comfy hotels and resorts that are near the national\r\n                    parks from our website. From budget-friendly accommodations to\r\n                    luxurious stays, we have got it all.</p>','<p>\r\n                    We specialize in curating tour packages for Kaziranga National Park\r\n                    which is located in Assam, India. Other than the tour packages, we\r\n                    also provide safari bookings and hotel bookings near the Kaziranga\r\n                    National Park. Our safari guides have good knowledge about the flora\r\n                    and fauna of the area. Our drivers know the park inside out and they\r\n                    know all the routes and other important rules related to safaris\r\n                    which ensure a nice trip. You can explore the beauty and wildness of\r\n                    the area without worrying about budget, convenience, or anything\r\n                    else.</p>','<p>\r\n                    We provide our service in a systematic way which is very important\r\n                    for a good and memorable trip. First of all, you make a booking on\r\n                    our platform, and after that, you are given a voucher which has the\r\n                    coordinator\'s number. He can call you, or you can also call him to\r\n                    arrange your meeting. Once the meeting point is fixed with the\r\n                    coordinator or you can say your tour assistant, he will take you for\r\n                    the safari ride. Be ready to explore the thrilling area while\r\n                    gaining knowledge about the same.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2024-05-13 05:56:44','2024-05-13 06:09:46'),(32,'attractions','Nearby Attraction','Nearby Attraction',NULL,'Nearby Attraction','Nearby Attraction','cghcfgcf','cghcgfh','<div class=\"kaziattraction\">\r\n                <div class=\"img-kg\">\r\n                    <img class=\"img-kg-1\" src=\"/front/assets/img/attraction/TEAGARDEN.webp\" alt=\"\">\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class=\"content-kg\">\r\n                    <h2>TEA GARDEN</h2>\r\n                    <p>\r\n                        There are many tea gardens near Kaziranga and these tea gardens\r\n                        are famous all over World. Everyone knows that Assam is famous for\r\n                        tea plantations so a visit to the tea garden should must be there\r\n                        on your list. Many visitors like to visit Hathkhuli, Borchappori,\r\n                        and a few other Tea Gardens. When visiting Kaziranga National\r\n                        Park, visitors must visit these tea plantations that should not be\r\n                        missed.\r\n                    </p>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"kaziattraction\">\r\n                <div class=\"content-kg\">\r\n                    <h2>KAKOCHANG WATERFALL</h2>\r\n                    <p>\r\n                        This is another popular picnic site near Kaziranga National Park.\r\n                        You can see the historical Numaligarh remnants from here. Another\r\n                        name for these waterfalls is Kakojan and it\'s a nice place to\r\n                        visit for taking good pictures and seeing beautiful views. From\r\n                        Bokakhat, the waterfall base is around 12 to 14 km and you can\r\n                        trek for approximately 04 kilometres to reach there.\r\n                    </p>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class=\"img-kg\">\r\n                    <img class=\"img-kg-1\" src=\"/front/assets/img/attraction/KAKOCHANGWATERFALL.webp\" alt=\"\">\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"kaziattraction\">\r\n                <div class=\"img-kg\">\r\n                    <img class=\"img-kg-1\" src=\"/front/assets/img/attraction/ORCHIDBIODIVERSITYPARK.webp\" alt=\"\">\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class=\"content-kg\">\r\n                    <h2>ORCHID BIODIVERSITY PARK</h2>\r\n                    <p>\r\n                        The Kaziranga National Orchid Park is a famous place among\r\n                        tourists, which covers an area of 6 acres. This park is just a\r\n                        distance of 2 km from Kaziranga and is located in Durgapur. Here\r\n                        you can find more than 500 different kinds of wild orchids, 46\r\n                        different kinds of bamboo, 12 different types of cane, 132\r\n                        different kinds of sour fruits and green veggies, with other flora\r\n                        species. Nature lovers should visit this park to learn about the\r\n                        wide range of flora of Assam.\r\n                    </p>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"kaziattraction\">\r\n                <div class=\"content-kg\">\r\n                    <h2>DEOPARBAT RUINS</h2>\r\n                    <p>\r\n                        The Ruins of Deoparbat are found near Kaziranga National Park.\r\n                        This place is located in Golaghat District which is 5 kilometers\r\n                        from Numaligarh. People also know this place as Deopahar which\r\n                        means 2 hills. On top of these hills, you can find an old temple\r\n                        with broken statues scattered around. These broken statues show\r\n                        their rich history. Climbing these hills is not an easy task, but\r\n                        once you’ve reached you can see amazing views of the surroundings.\r\n                    </p>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class=\"img-kg\">\r\n                    <img class=\"img-kg-1\" src=\"/front/assets/img/attraction/DEOPARBATRUINS.webp\" alt=\"\">\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"kaziattraction\">\r\n                <div class=\"img-kg\">\r\n                    <img class=\"img-kg-1\" src=\"/front/assets/img/attraction/HOOLLONGAPARGIBBONWILDLIFESANCTUARY.webp\" alt=\"\">\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class=\"content-kg\">\r\n                    <h2>HOOLLONGAPAR GIBBON WILDLIFE SANCTUARY</h2>\r\n                    <p>\r\n                        This wildlife sanctuary is located in the Jorhat district of Assam\r\n                        and it houses India’s only Ape family- The Hoolock Gibbons. This\r\n                        is the only sanctuary in India that is named after Gibbons. Seven\r\n                        out of fifteen apes live here and those are - western hoolock\r\n                        gibbon, Bengal slow loris, stump-tailed macaque, northern\r\n                        pig-tailed macaque, eastern Assamese macaque, rhesus macaque, and\r\n                        capped langur. Apart from them, a wide variety of bird species and\r\n                        snakes can also be found here.\r\n                    </p>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>','ccgbhc','chchb','chc',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2024-05-22 08:59:05','2024-05-24 06:10:13'),(33,'besttime','Best time to Visit','Best time to Visit',NULL,'Best time to Visit','Best time to Visit','cghcfgcf','cghcgfh','<div class=\"container \">\r\n                <p style=\"color: rgb(220, 220, 220)\">\r\n                    Kaziranga National Park is a famous tourist spot that remains open from October to April for safari\r\n                    rides. You can visit here on any day in these months during visiting hours. However, the best time to\r\n                    visit is from November to February. This is the dry season and the weather is also good for going on\r\n                    jeep and elephant safaris. These are the winter months and the temperate remains mild which is best for\r\n                    animal sightings. Many migratory birds also visit here during this time.\r\n                </p>\r\n\r\n                <div class=\"travelbox\" style=\"margin-top: 40px;\">\r\n                    <p style=\"color: rgb(218, 218, 218)\">\r\n                        You can also visit this park during March and April, in these 2 months the weather becomes hot and\r\n                        because of that people might not like the rides. However, if you do not have a problem with the\r\n                        humidity and heat then this can be a good time for spotting animals because they come near water\r\n                        bodies to drink it. Don’t forget to wear comfortable cotton clothes and bring your sunscreen and\r\n                        water bottles with you.\r\n\r\n                    </p>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class=\"travelbox\" style=\"margin-top: 40px;\">\r\n                    <p style=\"color: rgb(221, 221, 221)\">\r\n                        The park remains closed from 1st May to 30th September because of heavy rain in the area. During\r\n                        this time the Kaziranga forest land gets under the flood water of the Brahmaputra as most of the\r\n                        area is around the Brahmaputra river floodplains.\r\n                    </p>\r\n                </div>\r\n\r\n            </div>','ccgbhc','chchb','chc',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2024-05-22 08:59:05','2024-05-24 06:15:07'),(34,'bookingprocess','Online Safari Booking Process','Online Safari Booking Process',NULL,'Online Safari Booking Process','Online Safari Booking Process','bookingprocess','bookingprocess','<div class=\"container bkg_container\">\r\n            <div class=\"booking-content\">\r\n                <span class=\"fs-4\">1️⃣</span>\r\n                <span>\r\n                    Go to the website &nbsp;\r\n                    <a href=\"https://kazirangabooking.com/\">\r\n                        kazirangabooking.com</a></span>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"booking-content\">\r\n                <span class=\"fs-4\">2️⃣</span>\r\n                <span>Select the date, it is advised to book your safari ride 3 months\r\n                    before your trip</span>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"booking-content\">\r\n                <span class=\"fs-4\">3️⃣</span>\r\n                <span>\r\n                    Select the time slot, time slot depends on the month in which you’re\r\n                    planning your trip. There are 4 time slots available.</span>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"booking-content\">\r\n                <span class=\"fs-4\">4️⃣</span>\r\n                <span>\r\n                    Select the safari type - jeep, and elephant safari are available in\r\n                    Kaziranga National Park.</span>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"booking-content\">\r\n                <span class=\"fs-4\">5️⃣</span>\r\n                <span>\r\n                    Select the mode of safari, which means the zone in which you want to\r\n                    enjoy the safari.\r\n                </span>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"booking-content\">\r\n                <span class=\"fs-4\">6️⃣</span>\r\n                <span>\r\n                    After that, you need to enter the name of the person who is booking\r\n                    the Safari.\r\n                </span>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"booking-content\">\r\n                <span class=\"fs-4\">7️⃣</span>\r\n                <span> You have to provide your correct number and Email ID. </span>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"booking-content\">\r\n                <span class=\"fs-4\">8️⃣</span>\r\n                <span>\r\n                    Then a page will open, on that page you have to fill in the state\r\n                    from which you’re coming along with your full address. (Note: The\r\n                    address should be properly mentioned and match the identity you’re\r\n                    providing).\r\n                </span>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"booking-content\">\r\n                <span class=\"fs-4\">9️⃣</span>\r\n                <span>\r\n                    Then enter the details of passengers who are going on the jeep\r\n                    safari: like full name, age, gender, nationality, state, ID proof,\r\n                    and ID number (You have to fill in the complete and correct details\r\n                    of the passengers identity proof, failing which your booking would\r\n                    not be granted).\r\n                </span>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"booking-content\">\r\n                <span class=\"fs-4\">🔟</span>\r\n                <span>\r\n                    At last, you have to pay the amount that will be mentioned on the\r\n                    page.\r\n                </span>\r\n            </div>\r\n        </div>','bookingprocess','bookingprocess','chc',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2024-05-22 08:59:05','2024-05-24 06:26:22'),(35,'localfood','Local Food','Local Food',NULL,'Local Food','Local Food','localfood','localfood','<div class=\"container\">\r\n                <p style=\"color: rgb(220, 220, 220)\">\r\n                    Food is something that makes a connection between people from\r\n                    different regions. The food of a region reflects the culture and\r\n                    tradition of that place. The food of Assamm has its own style and\r\n                    pattern that is different from other states of India and other\r\n                    northeastern states. Kaziranga is located in the state of Assam and\r\n                    the food here is simple and flavourful. The staple foods or you can\r\n                    say the main ingredients here are rice, fish, meat, and vegetables\r\n                    with herbs. The traditional cooking style of this place is famous\r\n                    because of less use of spices. Because the spices are not used in\r\n                    quantity, one can taste the natural flavor of ingredients which\r\n                    makes the cuisines more flavourful. Some common methods such as\r\n                    fermentation and smoking are used here to cook the dishes. \"Bhoot\r\n                    Jolokia\" also known as ghost pepper is the hottest chili in the\r\n                    world and it is used here to make food. The cuisine of Assam is\r\n                    characterized as simple because the food here is less spicy as\r\n                    compared to other dishes. The food cooked here is much healthier and\r\n                    provides a natural flavor of the ingredients because of less use of\r\n                    herbs and vegetables and less use of spices. The cuisines that are\r\n                    prepared in this state are generally low in oil and spices but the\r\n                    exotic herbs, meat, and the Bhoot Jolokia add a strong flavor to the\r\n                    food.\r\n                </p>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"container\">\r\n                <div class=\"travelbox row\">\r\n                    <div class=\"localfood_section1_img col-lg-3 col-sm-12\">\r\n                        <img src=\"/front/assets/img/localfood/pitha.jpg\" alt=\"pitha\">\r\n                    </div>\r\n                    <div class=\"localfood_section_content col-lg-9 col-sm-12\">\r\n                        <h2>1. Pitha</h2>\r\n                        <p>\r\n                            This one is like the home-cooked rice cake and it’s one of the\r\n                            best snack time sides of Assam. People usually eat it during the\r\n                            morning for breakfast or in the evening with tea. Pitha can be\r\n                            sweet or savory, steamed or fried, and many varieties of this\r\n                            item can be found in households. Some different Pithas of Assam\r\n                            are ghila pitha, til pitha, bora pitha, narikol pitha, tekelir\r\n                            mukhot-diya pitha, bhaat pitha, luthuri pitha, sunga pitha, etc.\r\n                        </p>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                </div>\r\n\r\n                <div class=\"travelbox row\">\r\n                    <div class=\"localfood_section1_img col-lg-3 col-sm-12\">\r\n                        <img src=\"/front/assets/img/localfood/masortenga.jpg\" alt=\"\">\r\n                    </div>\r\n                    <div class=\"localfood_section_content col-lg-9 col-sm-12\">\r\n                        <h2>2. Masor Tenga</h2>\r\n                        <p>\r\n                            This one is a tangy fish curry that is light and has good taste.\r\n                            A gravy of tomatoes, elephant fruit, and lemon is made and then\r\n                            the local fish of Assam is slow-cooked in the gravy to make this\r\n                            delicious dish. The end result is a mouth-watering curry eaten\r\n                            with rice and some side dishes.\r\n                        </p>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                </div>\r\n\r\n                <div class=\"travelbox row\">\r\n                    <div class=\"localfood_section1_img col-lg-3 col-sm-12\">\r\n                        <img src=\"/front/assets/img/localfood/DuckMeatRecipes.jpg\" alt=\"\">\r\n                    </div>\r\n                    <div class=\"localfood_section_content col-lg-9 col-sm-12\">\r\n                        <h2>3. Duck Meat Recipes</h2>\r\n                        <p>\r\n                            This is a flavourful meat used in various Assam dishes. This\r\n                            meat is made mostly during festivals. Whole spices are used to\r\n                            make duck meat dishes and give the recipe a unique flavor. This\r\n                            meat can be cooked differently according to the preferences.\r\n                            Duck meat can be cooked with lentils, sesame, pumpkin, and other\r\n                            ingredients.\r\n                        </p>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                </div>\r\n\r\n                <div class=\"travelbox row\">\r\n                    <div class=\"localfood_section1_img col-lg-3 col-sm-12\">\r\n                        <img src=\"/front/assets/img/localfood/AlooPitika.jpg\" alt=\"\">\r\n                    </div>\r\n                    <div class=\"localfood_section_content col-lg-9 col-sm-12\">\r\n                        <h2>4. Aloo Pitika</h2>\r\n                        <p>\r\n                            This one is a comfort food of Assam that is served as a side\r\n                            dish with the main food. Assamese love this one a lot and mostly\r\n                            they have it with rice and dal. To make it, mashed potatoes are\r\n                            seasoned with mustard oil, onion, coriander, salt, and green\r\n                            chilies. This can be eaten at lunch or dinner. This kind of\r\n                            potato is delightfully simple and flavorsome.\r\n                        </p>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class=\"travelbox row\">\r\n                    <div class=\"localfood_section1_img col-lg-3 col-sm-12\">\r\n                        <img src=\"/front/assets/img/localfood/BambooShootFry.jpg\" alt=\"\">\r\n                    </div>\r\n                    <div class=\"localfood_section_content col-lg-9 col-sm-12\">\r\n                        <h2>5. Bamboo Shoot Fry</h2>\r\n                        <p>\r\n                            To make this, bamboo shoots are cleaned properly with water, and\r\n                            then they are stir-fried with spices. This is eaten with most of\r\n                            the dishes as a side dish that adds flavor to the food.\r\n                        </p>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                </div>\r\n\r\n                <div class=\"travelbox row\">\r\n                    <div class=\"localfood_section1_img col-lg-3 col-sm-12\">\r\n                        <img src=\"/front/assets/img/localfood/Khar.jpg\" alt=\"\">\r\n                    </div>\r\n                    <div class=\"localfood_section_content col-lg-9 col-sm-12\">\r\n                        <h2>6. Khar</h2>\r\n                        <p>\r\n                            It is one of the common dishes in the Assamese houses but this\r\n                            dish is uncommon to others. The aroma of this dish attracts\r\n                            people to have it more and more. The name of the dish is based\r\n                            on the main ingredient which is Khar. The magic that makes this\r\n                            dish amazing is the sun-dried banana peel. Mostly during\r\n                            festivals, you can find it in every household and people say\r\n                            that their celebrations are incomplete without this amazing\r\n                            dish.\r\n                        </p>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>','localfood','localfood','chc',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2024-05-22 08:59:05','2024-05-24 06:47:09'),(36,'localshopping','Local Shopping Outlets','Local Shopping Outlets',NULL,'Local Shopping Outlets','Local Shopping Outlets','localshopping','localshopping','<div class=\"container\">\r\n            <p class=\"my-2\">\r\n                Kaziranga National Park in Assam is famous because of its one-horned\r\n                rhinos and a lot of people come here to see them. The park is the main\r\n                attraction of this area but one can enjoy the culture of this place by\r\n                going to the local shopping outlets. By going there, you can immerse\r\n                yourself in the colors, flavors, and traditions of Assamese life.\r\n                Let’s learn about the famous shopping outlets of Kaziranga.\r\n            </p>\r\n\r\n            <div class=\"local_container\">\r\n                <div class=\"tea-img\">\r\n                    <div class=\"team_img_1\">\r\n                        <img class=\"team_image1\" src=\"/front/assets/img/localshop/Goodwyn Tea Retail Outlet.jpg\">\r\n                    </div>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class=\"tea-content\">\r\n                    <h2>Goodwyn Tea Retail Outlet</h2>\r\n                    <p class=\"text-secondary fw-bold\">\r\n                        <i class=\"bi bi-geo-alt\"></i> Hatikhuli, Kaziranga National Park\r\n                        Kohora More T.E, Kanchanjuri, Assam 785609\r\n                    </p>\r\n                    <p>\r\n                        As the name says, it’s a tea outlet and from here you can purchase\r\n                        multiple types of tea including Black Tea, Green Tea, Herbal Tea,\r\n                        Assam Tea, Darjeeling Tea, Tea bags, etc. They have been there in\r\n                        the industry since 2011 and opened their first store in 2019. They\r\n                        have 3 tea estates in Assam at Tinkharia, Sonajuli, and Dhullie.\r\n                        The ownership at tea estates allows them to control the entire\r\n                        production process and they only use the best leaves in their\r\n                        blends. Apart from their own stores, they provide it to more than\r\n                        1000 hotels, restaurants, cafes, and tea boutiques and they also\r\n                        have their own outlets at various airports. You can even try the\r\n                        taste and freshness of their tea as they have a cafe inside the\r\n                        outlets where you can spend a good time with family or friends\r\n                        while sipping fresh tea.\r\n                    </p>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n\r\n            <div class=\"local_container\">\r\n                <div class=\"tea-img\">\r\n                    <div class=\"team_img_1\">\r\n                        <img class=\"team_image1\" src=\"/front/assets/img/localshop/The Tea Cove Kaziranga NationalPark.jpg\">\r\n                    </div>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class=\"tea-content\">\r\n                    <h2>The Tea Cove Kaziranga National Park</h2>\r\n                    <p class=\"text-secondary fw-bold\">\r\n                        <i class=\"bi bi-geo-alt\"></i> Kaziranga National Park, Hatikhuli\r\n                        T.E., Assam 785609\r\n                    </p>\r\n                    <p>\r\n                        The Tea Cove is an exclusive place that sells and serves the best\r\n                        of Assamese Tea. After a tiring safari ride, you can enjoy your\r\n                        evening with a refreshing cup of tea. It’s a bakery and cake shop\r\n                        so you can also have delicious pastries and the cafe has an\r\n                        elegant ambiance. They also have coolers for summers to beat the\r\n                        heat of the sun. You can go here at any time of the day and spend\r\n                        as much time as you want, they won’t mind it. The staff at this\r\n                        cafe is very friendly and they serve everything with love. You can\r\n                        purchase from many different teas according to your liking.\r\n                    </p>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n\r\n            <div class=\"local_container\">\r\n                <div class=\"tea-img\">\r\n                    <div class=\"team_img_1\">\r\n                        <img class=\"team_image1\" src=\"/front/assets/img/localshop/Kaziranga Haat (Village Weaves).jpg\">\r\n                    </div>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class=\"tea-content\">\r\n                    <h2>Kaziranga Haat (Village Weaves)</h2>\r\n                    <p class=\"text-secondary fw-bold\">\r\n                        <i class=\"bi bi-geo-alt\"></i> 785609, Bocha Gaon, Assam\r\n                    </p>\r\n                    <p>\r\n                        Kaziranga Haat is a nice shopping outlet near the park. You can\r\n                        buy traditional handloom products such as doormats, tablemats,\r\n                        handbags, furniture, and many more from this shop. What makes\r\n                        these products different from other products sold in the area is\r\n                        that they are made from plastic waste. Rupjyoti Saikia Gogoi is a\r\n                        47-year-old woman who realized the problem of plastic waste on the\r\n                        streets. She came up with a ground-breaking idea of turning this\r\n                        waste into traditional handloom products back in 2004. She thought\r\n                        of weaving the waste just like she would do with bamboo. By\r\n                        following some simple steps, she integrated plastic with cotton\r\n                        threads to weave different products on a primitive handloom and\r\n                        has been following it since then. She made it possible with the\r\n                        help of other nearby ladies. Now she is making it possible for\r\n                        uneducated rural women to earn and make a living on their own by\r\n                        teaching them the technique. They have generated over Rs 3 lakh in\r\n                        the previous financial year.\r\n                    </p>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n\r\n            <div class=\"local_container\">\r\n                <div class=\"tea-img\">\r\n                    <div class=\"team_img_1\">\r\n                        <img class=\"team_image1\" src=\"/front/assets/img/localshop/Kohora Market.jpg\">\r\n                    </div>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class=\"tea-content\">\r\n                    <h2>Kohora Market</h2>\r\n                    <p class=\"text-secondary fw-bold\">\r\n                        <i class=\"bi bi-geo-alt\"></i> HCR2+24Q, Kohora, Assam 785609\r\n                    </p>\r\n                    <p>\r\n                        Kohora is a small town and it is the main entrance of Kaziranga\r\n                        National Park. It is between the Nagaon and Golaghat districts of\r\n                        Assam. There are many resorts, hotels, and guest houses in this\r\n                        area of Assam as it is the entrance point of the park. This is a\r\n                        market area with many departmental stores and you can find\r\n                        everything here including vegetables, hand-loom, organic tea,\r\n                        fish, repair shops, general stores, etc. It’s a perfect spot to\r\n                        find anything you need when coming to Kaziranga National Park.\r\n                    </p>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n\r\n            <div class=\"local_container\">\r\n                <div class=\"tea-img\">\r\n                    <div class=\"team_img_1\">\r\n                        <img class=\"team_image1\" src=\"/front/assets/img/localshop/Souvenir Shop Kaziranga.jpg\">\r\n                    </div>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class=\"tea-content\">\r\n                    <h2>Souvenir Shop Kaziranga</h2>\r\n                    <p class=\"text-secondary fw-bold\">\r\n                        <i class=\"fa-solid fa-location-dot\"></i> HCQ2+Q5Q, No.2 Sildubi,\r\n                        Kohora, Assam 785609\r\n                    </p>\r\n                    <p>\r\n                        There are many souvenir shops near Kaziranga. You can find them in\r\n                        the Kohora Market and also in the nearby areas. From the shops,\r\n                        you can purchase many beautiful handmade products. They have\r\n                        wooden carvings of wild animals as souvenirs and also beautiful\r\n                        handmade bags, mugs, showcases, and other local products. These\r\n                        souvenirs prove the best craftsmanship in the area. A visit to a\r\n                        souvenir shop should be there on your itinerary when visiting\r\n                        Kaziranga National Park\r\n                    </p>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n        </div>','localshopping','localshopping','chc',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2024-05-22 08:59:05','2024-05-24 06:30:18'),(37,'pricingtable','pricingtable','pricingtable',NULL,'pricingtable','pricingtable','pricingtable','pricingtable','pricingtable','pricingtable','pricingtable','chc',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2024-05-22 08:59:05','2024-05-22 08:59:05'),(38,'waterfalls','Beautiful Waterfalls','Beautiful Waterfalls',NULL,'Beautiful Waterfalls','Beautiful Waterfalls','waterfalls','waterfalls','<div class=\"container\">\r\n                <div class=\"section_1_waterfall row\">\r\n                    <div class=\"content-kg-water col-lg-6 col-sm-12\">\r\n                        <h2>Bhalukjuri Waterfalls</h2>\r\n                        <p>\r\n                            There are many tea gardens near Kaziranga and these tea\r\n                            gardens are famous all over World. Everyone knows that Assam\r\n                            is famous for tea plantations so a visit to the tea garden\r\n                            should must be there on your list. Many visitors like to\r\n                            visit Hathkhuli, Borchappori, and a few other Tea Gardens.\r\n                            When visiting Kaziranga National Park, visitors must visit\r\n                            these tea plantations that should not be missed.\r\n                        </p>\r\n                        <ul class=\"content-kg-waterlist\">\r\n                            <li>\r\n                                <span><i class=\"bi bi-check-circle-fill\"></i></span><span>This one doesn’t have any entry\r\n                                    fees or tickets.</span>\r\n                            </li>\r\n\r\n                            <li>\r\n                                <span><i class=\"bi bi-check-circle-fill\"></i></span><span>There is enough space for car\r\n                                    parking and to make\r\n                                    food.</span>\r\n                            </li>\r\n\r\n                            <li>\r\n                                <span><i class=\"bi bi-check-circle-fill\"></i></span><span>A small Shiva temple is also there\r\n                                    so you can take\r\n                                    blessings</span>\r\n                            </li>\r\n                        </ul>\r\n                    </div>\r\n\r\n                    <div class=\"img-kg-water image-hover-effect col-lg-6 col-sm-12\">\r\n                        <div class=\"waterfall-img\">\r\n                            <img class=\"waterfall_images2\" src=\"/front/assets/img/waterfall/Bhalukjuri Waterfalls S2.jpg\" alt=\"\">\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"waterfall-img2\">\r\n                            <img class=\"waterfall_images2\" src=\"/front/assets/img/waterfall/Bhalukjuri Waterfalls.jpg\" alt=\"\">\r\n                        </div>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class=\"container-second row\">\r\n                    <div class=\"image-hover-effect secondimagesdiv col-lg-6 col-sm-12 order-lg-1 order-2\">\r\n                        <div class=\"second_img_water1\">\r\n                            <img src=\"/front/assets/img/waterfall/kangthilangsowaterfall.jpg\">\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"second_img_water2\">\r\n                            <img src=\"/front/assets/img/waterfall/kangthilangsowaterfall S2.jpg\">\r\n                        </div>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                    <div class=\"content-kg-water2 col-lg-6 col-sm-12 order-lg-2 order-1\">\r\n                        <h2>Kaipholangso Waterfalls / Kakochang Waterfall</h2>\r\n                        <p>\r\n                            Kakochang Waterfalls is a famous tourist place and locals\r\n                            know it as Kaipholangso waterfalls. You can relax in the\r\n                            natural surroundings and see some beautiful views here. It’s\r\n                            a good picnic spot near the world-famous Kaziranga National\r\n                            Park. The remains of the historical Numaligarh are near to\r\n                            this area and they can be seen from here. It’s a nice picnic\r\n                            spot that is located about 13 km from the Bokakhat. This\r\n                            trek needs at least a day to explore it well so if you’re\r\n                            coming to Kaziranga and you’re interested in trekking then a\r\n                            visit to Kakochang waterfall should be there on your list.\r\n                            If you’re going towards Kakochang then grab some snacks and\r\n                            food with you as no food outlets are available there. Some\r\n                            famous tourist attractions near this waterfall include the\r\n                            ruins of Numaligarh, the ruins of Deoparbat or Deopahar, and\r\n                            landscapes of tea, coffee, and rubber farms.\r\n                        </p>\r\n                        <ul class=\"content-kg-waterlist\">\r\n                            <li>\r\n                                <span><i class=\"bi bi-check-circle-fill\"></i></span><span>Kakochang Waterfalls is a famous\r\n                                    tourist place.</span>\r\n                            </li>\r\n\r\n                            <li>\r\n                                <span><i class=\"bi bi-check-circle-fill\"></i></span><span>Historical Numaligarh are near to\r\n                                    this area.</span>\r\n                            </li>\r\n                            <li>\r\n                                <span><i class=\"bi bi-check-circle-fill\"></i></span><span>Historical Numaligarh are near to\r\n                                    this area.</span>\r\n                            </li>\r\n\r\n                            <li>\r\n                                <span><i class=\"bi bi-check-circle-fill\"></i></span><span>It’s a good picnic spot near the\r\n                                    world-famous Kaziranga\r\n                                    National Park.</span>\r\n                            </li>\r\n                        </ul>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                </div>\r\n\r\n                <div class=\"container_3 row\">\r\n                    <div class=\"content_3 col-lg-6 col-sm-12\">\r\n                        <h2>kangthilangso waterfall</h2>\r\n                        <p>\r\n                            Kangthilangso Waterfalls is situated in the Delhiram Goan of\r\n                            Assam near Kaziranga. You can go here with family and\r\n                            friends. It’s a scenic view to see the water flowing down a\r\n                            rocky cliff and into a deep pool below. It’s a popular\r\n                            tourist destination among locals and people who come from\r\n                            different areas. This Kangthilangso Waterfall remains quiet\r\n                            busy on weekends. But on weekdays and mornings, it remains\r\n                            peaceful and you can enjoy the calmness and natural vibes\r\n                            here. There is a large area for picnic near the waterfalls\r\n                            so you can spend a good time with family and friends after\r\n                            coming here. The ticket price to go to this waterfall is INR\r\n                            Rupees 50 for one person.\r\n                        </p>\r\n                        <ul class=\"content-kg-waterlist\">\r\n                            <li>\r\n                                <span><i class=\"bi bi-check-circle-fill\"></i></span><span>There is a large area for picnic\r\n                                    near the\r\n                                    waterfalls</span>\r\n                            </li>\r\n                            <li>\r\n                                <span><i class=\"bi bi-check-circle-fill\"></i></span><span>This waterfall is a beautiful\r\n                                    natural attraction of the\r\n                                    area.</span>\r\n                            </li>\r\n                        </ul>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                    <div class=\"image_3 col-lg-6 col-sm-12\">\r\n                        <div class=\"kangimagecontainer\">\r\n                            <img src=\"/front/assets/img/waterfall/Bhalukjuri Waterfalls S2.jpg\" alt=\"\">\r\n\r\n                            <div class=\"small_content\">\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    This waterfall is around <b>142</b> km from the park and\r\n                                    it’s a nice place to plan a picnic.\r\n                                </p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>','waterfalls','waterfalls','chc',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2024-05-22 08:59:05','2024-05-24 06:45:04');
